The President of the United States, along with his wife Michelle, released a statement in support of the International Day Against Homophobia and Transphobia. They emphasized that LGBT rights are human rights and that all individuals deserve to live without fear, violence, or discrimination. The President mentioned efforts being made to end bias-motivated violence, combat workplace discrimination, and address the needs of transgender individuals within the country. He also expressed pride in the United States' efforts to prioritize LGBT rights in global diplomacy. The President acknowledged that there is still much work to be done, but promised to continue fighting until everyone can live with equality and dignity.